 qemu-server (9.1.19) trixie; urgency=medium
 
   * fix #3711: allow removing a VM even if one of its storages no longer
     exists, instead of aborting the removal and leaving the VM behind. Related
     handling of storage errors was made more robust and consistent:
     - check that a volume's storage still exists before the ownership check,
       and warn instead of silently continuing on a storage error
     - warn and continue if the linked-clone check errors out, as it runs again
       later and still blocks removal when clones exist
     - log the remaining storage and disk-free errors as warnings for
